                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 718.1915/218.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Cresson</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation”</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-22T10:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 22, 1914, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to Legation’s telegram of October 1, Costa Rican boundary decision was
                    rejected by the Foreign Relations commission of the Panama Congress for the
                    reason that fluvial not mountain line was fixed upon. Panaman President informed
                    Panaman Congress similar decision has already been telegraphed Washington and
                    Costa Rica. Panaman Congress approved executive action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cresson</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
